    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the naturally aspirated 3.6L M96 flat-six, producing 320hp through a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. The drivetrain is exceptionally tight, benefiting from a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal. The suspension geometry remains true, utilizing its multi-link rear setup and McPherson struts to deliver signature feedback. Deceleration is handled by four-piston Monobloc calipers over vented rotors with zero fade. This example boasts a clean borescope report and a dry undercarriage, representing a mechanically sound driver's car for the purist who values visceral throttle response and chassis rigidity.",
      "price": 32500.0,
